  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project manager (Cheque clearing)",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for experienced professionals to support a project related to <strong>Singapore cheque clearing for SGD and USD</strong>. The ideal candidates must have <strong>hands-on domain knowledge and prior experience</strong> in Singapore’s cheque clearing processes, systems, and regulatory requirements.</p><p>Both roles require strong understanding of the operational and technical workflows involved in cheque clearing within the Singapore banking ecosystem.</p><p><strong>1. Project Manager (PM)</strong></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Lead and manage end-to-end delivery of the Singapore cheque clearing project (SGD & USD).</li><li>Coordinate with internal teams, external vendors, and stakeholders.</li><li>Develop project plans, timelines, and progress reports.</li><li>Identify project risks and drive mitigation strategies.</li><li>Ensure compliance with MAS and local clearing regulations.</li><li>Facilitate project meetings and document key decisions.</li><li>Oversee user acceptance testing (UAT) and implementation activities.</li></ul><p><strong>Required Skills & Experience:</strong></p><ul><li>Proven experience as a Project Manager in banking or financial services.</li><li>Mandatory: Prior experience in Singapore cheque clearing domain.</li><li>Strong understanding of cheque clearing workflows, systems, and regulations.</li><li>Excellent communication, stakeholder management, and documentation skills.</li></ul><p>Ability to manage cross-functional teams and drive on-time delivery</p>",
